article.description: — KJ Johnson matched his career high with 25 points as Lipscomb easily defeated NAIA-member Freed-Hardeman 93-72 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Johnson carries Lipscomb over Freed-Hardeman 93-72
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- — KJ Johnson matched his career high with 25 points as Lipscomb easily defeated NAIA-member Freed-Hardeman 93-72 on Tuesday night. Johnson made 10 of 12 shots. Romeao Ferguson had 16 points for Lipscomb (5-5). Carson Cary added 14 points. Tommy Murr had 10 points. Lipscomb posted a season-high 18 3-pointers. Lipscomb totaled 49 second-half points, a season high for the team. Jon Moore had 13 points for the Lions. Logan Bonds added 12 points. Ryley McClaran had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
